Using the formula given in the hint, we know that the median \emph{m}
must satisfy the integral:

\begin{align*}\frac12 = \int_0^m \frac3{\pi} \frac1{1+t^2}\,dt\end{align*}

Thus, we evaluate the integral above and then solve for \emph{m}.

\begin{align*}
\frac12 &= \int_0^m \frac3{\pi} \frac1{1+t^2}\,dt  \\
&=  \frac3{\pi}\arctan(m) \end{align*}

hence $m = \tan(\pi/6) = 1/\sqrt{3}$.

(Or $m = \tan(\frac{\arctan \sqrt{3}}2)$.)
